{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112201/0394.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE SIX\nConservation\nFarming News\nWeekly Items Os Interest To\nAshe Farmers\nBy j. t. mclaurin\nThe New River Soil Conserva\ntion District recently assisted\nMoody Hale, of the Helton com\nmunity, establish contour guides\non more than 30 acres of his farm.\n\u201cI do not plan to crop any of my\nfarm without following a system\nof stripcropping and now is the\ntime to start,\u201d Mr. Hale said.\n\nW. L. McMillan, of the Scott\nville community has planted\nmore than 10,000 white pines on\na badly eroded field on his farm\nand is so well pleased with the\nresults that he plans to plant the\nrest of the field in pines this win\nter. \u201cI did not think anything\nwould grow on that field when\nI bought it but it will not be but\na very few years until a good\ncrop of timber can be cut there,\u201d\nMr. McMillan stated.\nHayden Goodman, of the Bea\nver Creek community, says he is\nconvinced that now is the time\nof the year to apply lime and\nphosphate to pastures. He says\nmany farmers do not treat their\npastures until spring and they\ndo not get the full benefits from\nmaterials for another year.\nG. M. Campbell, chief clerk of\nthe AAA Office, says lime and\nphosphate received by the farm\ners on this year\u2019s program must\nbe applied before the last of the\nyear or no credit will be given on\nthe 1945 Program. Farmers who\ndo not have their materials ap\nplied before this date will not be\nallowed the full amount they\ncould get on the 1946 Program.\nAny reduction in the number of\nacres farmers of Ashe county\ntreat, means a reduction in yields\nof crops and an increase in the\namount of erosion on the farms\ndue to insufficient cover for the\nfields, he explained.\nSjssj. It's Not All Corn\n[this piece\n...J A\nIWENn/-WE fSHGED IFI s//\nHUNPRED Pt6HTAT PINNERUSTMjW/M\u00ae Is\u00ae V\nS MOPE IM\nI WAR 6ONDS7 MARiE.ypu was th\nSMARTEST MAM W\nf THIS COUNTY. I\n\nvC\nI\nWanted: Peeled\nLocust Posts\noOo\ns.\nlam now in the market for several thousand peeled locust posts. If\ninterested in producing some of these during the next 60 or 90 days, see or\nwrite me at Lansing, N. C., for prices and specifications.\nJ. O. Blevins\noOo\nThe Service Store\nLANSING, NORTH CAROLINA\nj\nflUi /4b fl b' \"i\n\nPOEM WINS SSOO BOND: Ruth Winslow\nGordon of Georgetown, O.\u2014 kin of Longfel- .3\nlow, Bryant and Bryon\u2014captures top award >s\nfor the poem she wrote in a national\nMmHaSall BljgiMtaWomen\u2019s Club flower program. Here she\nrece v \u00aes her 5500 bond from W. E. Joy, j,\npresident (left), and Chas. Meyers, district WW|* 7\nI i officer, of Florists\u2019 Telegraph Delivery Assn.\n11\nATOMIC AGE JEW- T ''i- W\nj: ELRY HAS ARRIVED!\nA torn si's?, the \u2019used Sgns\u00dffr\nearth taken from the\nA bomb testing area in sBIBSBff 4\nNew Mexico. mounted\nv v\u2019v 5 in white palladium, the c 'J S\u25a0' -wl? \u2022>\u20193\nx s -vv most modern of precious s *ssf 3\nj metals, is shown above\nin headdress and ear-\nfe- A v rings designed by Marc THE WINNAH! Lovely Eleanor Cahill\nx; Koven, New York Jew- of Coronado, California, was selected\ngKfe/ f'?' \u00aelry designer. Atomsite as \u201cMiss Stardust of 1945\u2019\u2019 in a nation-,\nBwsgg&W w-. is a green glassy sub- wide beauty contest. She is wearing a\nstance looking somewhat \u201cStardust\u201d tailored blouse, from which 1\n\u2019x\u2019 i'ke Jade. Palladium is she got her title, which is guaranteed\u2019\n|\u00a3@k .\u2022\u25a0/.,.7. the newest element in to give one year\u2019s wear, the period'\nJewelry, a white precious which \u201cMiss Stardust\u201d holds her title.'\nX-' metal rarer than gold\nv i but in the gold price\nZ range. The headdress\nbrooch has curving ellip-\nV .s s's. tical and concentric bars\nj?'*?>& of palladium surround- BEFORE V-J DAY, men depended on\n.\u25a0'\u25a0i -z.x-.V'.-x/ inn the inch-and-a-haif this automatic electric floating water\n''WaSBA '\"Ov-- oval shaped atomsite lisht, shown below, for rescue at sea,\nkz-. 5\u00aeU\nHs in center. Koven Water Light Corporation, New York,\nt to symbolize the 14 is now available for the safety of\nar theory. yachtsmen on pleasure craft.\na\nKi 'fe ;M.d\nTHERE\u2019LL BE MUSIC in the Air Mayor La Guardia L\" v 1\nof New York bids Godspeed to Edwin Franko Goldman, 7 \u2022.z\nfamous bandmaster, who is leaving for a tour of the x\nPacific for USO-Camp Shows, a National War Fund\nservice. Goldman will organize and lead bands of service TSi, '3i\nmen in the Pacific Occupation forces. s\u25a0 e\nTimely Hints\nBy RUTH CURRENT\nWith the aid of an ordinary\nfood or meat chopper the home\ncook can convert some of this\nfall\u2019s abundant nuts to butter or\npaste for sandwich fillings. These\nbutters may be used in soup,\nscalloped vegetables, stuffing, and\nomelet, or as part of the fat in\nbiscuits, cookies and cup cakes.\nFor a half pound of peanut but\nter: 2 cups blanched and roasted\nnuts; 1 tablespoon bland table\noil; x /i teaspoon salt. Grind\nthrough finest plate of the chop\nper twice or three times until the\nnuts have the consistency of but\nter. Add oil and salt. Mix well\nand pack in a tight container.\n\u201cThe egg is the cement that\nholds the castles of cookery to\ngether,\u201d once said a famous chef.\nYou may use eggs to thicken a\ncustard or sauce, to leaven or\nlighten a souffle or cake, to hold\ntogether oil and vinegar in a\nfHE SKYLAND POST, WEST JEFFERSON, N. C.\ncreamy mayonnaise. Use egg\nwhites to make cloudy soups\nclear, or an egg shall with some\nof the white still clinging to\n\u201csettle\u201d muddy coffee.\nFlat omelets, fluffy omelets\u2014\nwhichever you like, the ingredi\nents are the same. One or two\neggs for each person, 1 table\nspoon of milk for each egg, and\nsalt and pepper to taste. To make\nomelets fluffy, beat the egg yolks\nand whites separately. For a\nflat omelet, beat all ingredients\ntogether.\nA gentle squeeze is better than\nthe usual twist of the wrist for\nremoving water from a sweater\nor other knitted garment after\nwashing, say textile specialists.\nThe twisting and stretching of\nwringing may pull the wet wool\nso far out of shape that the\nsweater may never regain its ori\nginal size. The specialists advise\ngathering the sweater in a ball\nbetween the two hands and gent-\nIly squeezing or pressing the wa\nter from it. Then, if the color is\nfast, it may be rolled up in a bath\ntowel for an hour or two. The\ntowel will absorb moisture. Fi\nnally, lay the sweater flat and\nshaped to its correct size to dry.\nDon\u2019t let the boys down \u2014buy\nVictory Bonds NOW!\nRelief At Last\nForYourCough\nCreomulsion relieves promptly be\ncause it goes right to the seat of the\ntrouble to help loosen and expel\ngerm laden phlegm, and aid nature\nto soothe and heal raw, tender, in\nflamed bronchial mucous mem\nbranes. Tell your druggist to sell you\na bottle of Creomulsion with the un\nderstanding you must like the way it\nquickly allays the cough or you axe\nto have your money back.\nCREOMULSION\nfor Coughs, Chest Colds, Bronchitis\nI The Middles By Bob Karp\nBA.ee you Dopsy?t| l[ are you\nSUlf2E.yOUVt\\ NONSENSE, 5u2E >OLfRB SUBE-\nHAD ENOU<SH IIMASB\u00aeGHT AWAKE, DEAR? I AND fj\nSLEEP-yOU J AND O4IPPE2 .-\u2014*4 RAPIN' \u00aeSEt\nCHRTAiNL-y Jas-ho-hum- j/ It go! 6\ngVE^> 7 w* p\nA\\i\u00a3&4# s6k\nmMtaSMiSMi\n1*- r\nBehind\nYour Bonds\nLies the Might of America\ng|y||jMKjL\nJ7 r\nTHRIVING CITY\nPopulated by 3,785 persons in 1880,\nAlbuquerque, N. M., is the State\u2019s\nlargest city with 35,378. Packing\nplants, canning factories, the grow\ning State University, railway shops,\ntile and metal works make it hum.\nIts annual payroll of over S3O mil\nlion hints at the riches it will con\ntribute to back Victory Bonds.\nU. S. Treasury Department\nNOTICE OF ADMINISTRATION\nMrs. Nell B. Phipps, having\nqualified as Administratrix of\nthe estate of J. F. Phipps, deceas\ned, late of Ashe County, North\nCarolina, this is to notify all per\nsons having claims against the\nestate of said deceased to exhibit\nthem to the undersigned at\nCrumpler, North Carolina, on or\nbefore the Bth day of November,\n1946, or this notice will be pleaded\nin bar of their recovery. All per\nsons indebted to said estate will\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 2nd day of November,\n1945.\nMrs. Nell B. Phipps, Admin\nistratrix of J. F. Phipps, de\nceased. 11-8-6 t\nNOTICE OF SALE\nIN THE SUPERIOR COURT\nBEFORE THE CLERK\nNORTH CAROLINA\nASHE COUNTY\nMargaret C. Carter, General\nGuardian of Mattie Cowles Steel,\nExparte\nBy virtue of an order of the\nSuperior Court of Ashe County\nmade in the above entitled pro\nceeding, I, Ira T. Johnston, Com\nmissioner, will sell to the highest\nbidder for cash at the Courthouse\ndoor in Jefferson, North Carolina,\nat one o\u2019clock, P. M., on the 3rd\nday of December, 1945, the fol\nlowing described land, to-wit:\nFirst Tract: A one sixth undi\nvided interest in a tract of land\ncontaining 84 acres, known as\ntract No. 3-B on Pine Creek as\nshown on plat and sub-division of\nCowles land recorded in the of\nfice of the Clerk of the Superior\nCourt of Ashe County.\nSecond Tract: A tract of land\ncontaining 23 1-3 acres, more or\nless, it being a one-sixth part of\nLot No. 3 as shown on the plat of\nClover Hill farm of the land of\nLindsy Patterson as recorded in\nthe office of the Clerk of the\nSuperior Court of Caldwell\nCounty.\nThis November 1, 1945.\nIra T. Johnston, Commis\nsioner. 11-8-4 t\nAttention!\nWORLD WAR TWO\nVETERAN\nWould you like to learn\nthe printing trade under\nthe G. I. Bill of Rights vo\ncational assistance pro*\ngram? If so, contact us.\nThis program will enable\nyou to earn good pay and\nlearn at the same time. We\nhave filed application to\nparticipate in this activity\nand will have an opening\nsoon. Come in and let\u2019s\ntalk things over. Prefer\nyoung man with high school\neducation.\nThe Skyland Post\nWest Jefferson, N. C.\nFor Quick Results, Use The Post\u2019s\nCLASSIFIED ADS\nRATES TO BUY TO SELL\nMinimum of 35c per issue of\nnot more than 25 words. For TO RENT \u2014TO FIND\neach additional word over 25,\nl'/ 2 c per word. L. J\nAll \u201ckeyed\u201d classified ads HiVeryDOCiy\nare minimum of 50c.\nCards of Thanks, 50c Reads The\nMemorials and Obituaries,\n$1 T s e\u00b0 rm Tc m X Classifieds\nFOR SALE\u2014SS acre farm in\none tract, 33 acres in second tract.\nGood buildings on both places.\nWell timbered. See Garland Dol\nlar, Warrensville, N. C.\n11-22-3tp\nWANTED TO BUY About\n10 acres of land in or near Jes\nferson. Contact Mrs. Wilbert\nBresler, c-o Mrs. Gordon White\n'ner, Warrensville, N. C. 11-l-4tp\n1\nRecent experiment station stud\nies indicate that careful baking\ntime, followed by prompt serving,\nis important for saving vitamin\nC in Irish potatoes. Overbaking\nresults in considerable loss of the\nvitamin.\nPAROLE NOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nASHE COUNTY\nNotice is hereby given that\nWade Blackburn, who was con\nvicted at the April term, 1939, of\nthe Superior Court of Ashe Coun\nty for assault with deadly wea\npon with intent to kill, has made\napplication to Honorable Hatha\nway Cross, Commissioner of Pa\nroles, for admission to parole.\nThis November 14, 1945.\nWade Blackburn.\n11-22-2tc\nATHLETES FOOT GERM\nEasy To Kill\nIn One Hour, if not pleased, get\nyour 35c back. At any drug\nstore, get this strong fungicide,\nTE-OL. Contains 90% alchohol.\nThis makes it PENETRATE.\nReaches and kills more germs.\nApply Full Strength for itchy,\nsweaty feet or F. O. (foot odor).\nToday at Ray Drug Co.\n11-l-4tc\nLocal Business Directory\nWe Have Material In Stock ReinS-StlirdivaUt\nportrait\n\u2014and\u2014 runeral Home\nENLARGEMENT WORK\n3 Day Delivery On Finished\nWork Licensed Embalmers And\nThe Picture Shop Funeral Directors\nPHONE 88\nOver Harrison s Case\nLansing, N. C. WEST JEFFERSON, N. C.\nCOU \u2019dAY or NIGHT Lai